               <p>HENRY MARTIN. I was in <placeName id="t18171203-15-crimeloc88">Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18171203-15-crimeloc88" type="placeName" value="Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18171203-15-crimeloc88" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18171203-15-off86 t18171203-15-crimeloc88"></join> on the 15th of November, at half-past eight o'clock in the evening, passing where the houses are being pulled down. I felt some person pull the tail of my coat, I put my hand down, missed my handkerchief, turned round, and found the prisoner at my elbow, in great confusion, putting the handkerchief under his waistcoat. I collared him - He said I had mistaken the person. I took him into a shop to search him. As I was going in at the door, he took it out and threw it on the pavement-he begged for mercy.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
